President Biden addressed a group of emergency response personnel in a call regarding the approaching Hurricane Ida. He thanked them for their hard work and dedication, acknowledging the challenges they have faced with previous disasters and the ongoing COVID-19 response. President Biden emphasized the importance of preparedness and ensuring the safety of people in the region. He mentioned that an emergency declaration has been signed for Louisiana and that FEMA personnel and supplies have been deployed to the affected areas. The President urged people to pay attention to local authorities, have necessary supplies on hand, and follow COVID-19 safety precautions. He then handed the conversation over to Administrator Criswell for an update and to discuss any additional needs.